doc_summary_long: The United Kingdom will double its fleet of armed drones, defense secretary Michael Fallon announced on Saturday, under a $125m (£100m) development deal with US arms manufacturer General Atomics. General Atomics, makers of the Predator and Reaper drones used widely by the US, will provide 10 drones to the Royal Air Force, bringing the fleet from 10 to 20.
doc_summary_short: The United Kingdom will double its fleet of armed drones, defense secretary Michael Fallon announced on Saturday, under a $125m (£100m) development deal with US arms manufacturer General Atomics.
doc_title: UK to double armed drone fleet in deal with US Predator manufacturer
